          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 71</h1><p><strong>Questions 11 - 15</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>11 How does Kevin feel about the amount of waste that is recycled in Bookwall?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    hopeful that it will start improving</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    surprised that it is so high</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    pleased with the progress that has been made</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>12 What point is Kevin making when he talks about drinks cans?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    People should ideally avoid buying canned drinks.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Recycling an item uses less energy than making a new one would.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Before buying a product, it is worth checking whether packaging can be recycled.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>13 Kevin mentions ships in order to</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    explain how much waste is produced.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    warn how dangerous rubbish in the sea can be.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    point out that a lot of the UK’s rubbish is sent overseas.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>14 What children’s activity is being organised this year?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    making something out of recycled objects</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    writing a story about recycling</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    photographing people recycling</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>15 What does Kevin say about the recycling centres in Bookwall?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    They are easy to get to.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Several new ones have recently opened.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    They are good places to learn about recycling.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
